      • perPredicateNodeIterator

        public static Iterator<Node> perPredicateNodeIterator(GraphFacade.NodeIterateStrategy nodeIterateStrategy,
                                                      Node startNode,
                                                      Predicate<Node>... nodeIterateOrderPredicates)
        Creates a predicated Node iterator that iterates the Node s per Predicate that is specified using the GraphFacade.NodeIterateStrategy.

        Take the following node structure for example 

                           A
      +------------+------------+
      B            C            D
 +----+----+       |        +---+------------+
 E    F    G       H        I   J            K
                                      +------+------+
                                      L      M      N

        If we assume that we have 3 Predicates

        • The 1. Predicate matches Nodes A,C,H,D,K
        • The 2. Predicate matches Nodes A,B,E,F
        • The 3. Predicate matches Nodes D,J,M,N
        and we construct a per predicated node iterator using 
         GraphFacade.perPredicatedNodeIterator(BREADTH_FIRST, startNodeA, pred1, pred2, pred3);

        The resulting iterator will iterate the node structure using a breadth first strategy for every Predicate starting at startNodeA.
        The result will be: 

         breadth first  breadth first   breadth first
   matching       matching       matching
    pred1          pred2           pred3
 +-----------+   +-------+       +-------+
   A C D H K      A B E F         D J M N

 iterate order -->

        Parameters:
        nodeIterateStrategy -
        startNode -
        nodeIterateOrderPredicates -
        Returns:
